  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a dry, large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until charred all over then set aside for later</p>\n<p>Tip: Open a window or turn your extraction on, as this may get smoky!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>chipotle paste</strong>, <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>dried chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cumin</strong> to a large plate with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and stir it all together</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>rump steaks</strong> to the plate and give everything a good mix up until fully coated in the spices</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice most of the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and finely dice the rest</p>\n<p>Deseed the <strong>green pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dice the <strong>tomatoes </strong>finely<strong> </strong>and add them to the bowl with the <strong>diced red onion</strong></p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>charred</strong> <strong>red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> finely (don't like spice? Deseed your chillies!) and add to the same bowl </p>\n<p>Add a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and the <strong>juice</strong> of the<strong> lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and stir it all together – this is your <strong>charred chilli salsa </strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2203.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
